history.content:
Last year it seemed like they started getting people off the waitlist right around adjustment time, but it also looked like it also started happening the day after rising sophomores finished registration.  I think today was the start of sophomore registration if I’m not mistaken, so it is possible that as early as Friday they could start releasing some from waitlist.

In any event, everyone who got on waitlist up to now should get in eventually.

When will the reserved seats for CS61B be opened up? I thought that by phase 2 these spots would be opened, but I'm still way up on the waitlist and now I don't know if I'll get into the class at all.

I'm a bioengineering major (which is CoE) and I wanted to get into CS61B and EE16A so I could declare a double major in EECS after this fall but I didn't get into either class :-(

Edit: Just saw that it doesn't open up till the 18th. Still, I'm worried that even if I get into the lectures, I won't be able to get a good lab or discussion for EE16A. Anyone know what the likelihood of being able to get a Tuesday/Thursday lab for EE16A is?
